          <!--Hieron son of Hierokles, basileus hagemon, to all the gods, by the Syracusans. Syracuse museum basement, where I have now seen myself and have photographs. Large base, in dense gray ?marble. Debate concerns whether one can restore 'hagemonos' in line 1, b/c this is important for Hieron's title (basileus kai hegemon?). Note Ma, Statues and Cities (2013) 20 n.27 for this base as the *only* one where the honorand is in the genitive: 'the formulation i nthe genitive is anomalous and in fact the nature of this base 'of king Hieron', dedicated to the gods, is unclear.'--></p></div><div type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl type="IG"><citedRange><ref target="https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760">14.0002</ref></citedRange><ptr target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F"/></bibl><bibl type="SEG"><citedRange>56.1103.1.1<!--Failed to convert--></citedRange><ptr target="http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ"/></bibl><bibl type="CIG"><citedRange>3.5368</citedRange><ptr target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/HTUDQBXS"/></bibl><bibl type="SGDI"><citedRange>3231</citedRange><ptr target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JB4GMPBH"/></bibl><bibl><author>Dittenberger</author><date>1915-1924</date><citedRange>no.427</citedRange><ptr target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/XP5NMDKZ"/></bibl><bibl><author>De Sensi Sestito</author><date>1977</date><citedRange>82</citedRange><ptr target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/C9XXW8IX"/></bibl><bibl><author>Libertini</author><date>1929</date><citedRange>123</citedRange><ptr target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/AHZ3TB5P"/></bibl><bibl><author>Dimartino</author><date>2006</date><citedRange>no.1.1</citedRange><ptr target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/7AQ7W2MW"/></bibl></listBibl></div></body></text></TEI>